You should place your iPhone into a water proof bag and to ease the starting of the app, you can tap “Start” up to 60 minutes before you actually start your water activities.  The app will automatically start recording your activity when you start paddling.

SUP provides advantages over most other GPS-based apps: 

• Easier to use with an auto-pause feature 
• Does not require WiFi or cellular connection
• No logon required and all data is stored locally
• Record waypoints with optional photos
• Can get you “Back on Time” or “Back by Dark”
• Allows you to trace your way back
• A GPS auto shut-off battery saver
• App can be resumed if terminated for any reason

EASY TO USE
Just tap “Start” when you are at your SUP or kayaking lunch point and the app will “wait” for you to start your activities.  With SUP, there is no account setup required.  No registration required.  It does not even require a Wi-Fi or cell phone connection, just a GPS signal.  SUP operates in the background so you can use your iPhone to make and receive phone calls, play music, or run other apps all the while SUP is tracking your activity.

AUTO-PAUSE 
SUP has an auto-pause feature that allows you to pause up to 60 minutes (by default, settable to 5-60 minutes in Settings) before the app asks you if your activity has “Ended?”  With Auto Pause, only the time you are actively moving is used to calculate your average speed.

BACK-ON-TIME
Have you ever got caught out after it’s too dark to see or got back latter than you want?  This is because you didn’t know when to head-back to be back on time.  With SUP, all you need to do is set the “Return Time” or select “Back by Dark” and the app does the rest.  It alerts you when it is time to head-back, displays how fast you need to go, and your current speed.  It also displays an Estimated Time of Arrival (ETA) back at your starting point based on your current location and speed.  

With SUP, you can set the “Return Time” when you start your activity or anytime during your activity and you can even choose a different route back and SUP can still get you back-on-time!   

SAVE AND SHARE YOUR ACTIVITIES
The app automatically saves your route map and activity details locally on your iPhone.  You can share your route map and activity details via email or Facebook,  The app can also assist you in marking any number of waypoints and allowing you to include any number of photos with each waypoint.  At any time you can email the waypoint locations and optional photos to anyone.  This is great to let others know about hazards, points of interest or setting a future meeting location.

BATTERY SAVING  
The app can automatically detects when you have ended your activity and shuts off the GPS to save your battery.
 
FEATURE SUMMARY
• Very easy to use
• Very accurate
• No account setup required
• No registration required
• Displays time, distance and calories
• Displays average and current speed

• Resume terminated activities

DISCLAIMER
Continued use of GPS running in the background can dramatically decrease battery life.  With SUP a single battery charge can provide over 24 hours of use on an iPhone.

Hanglage ist die einzige App im Appstore die von Skitourengehern für Skitourengeher gemacht wurde. Am Berg ist sehr oft kein Netz. Diese App speichert die Berichte und du kannst sie am Berg ohne Probleme nochmals durchlesen.

HangLage, ist der ideale Begleiter bei jeder Skitour/Snowboardtour oder Bergtour im Winter. Diese App hilft dir dein Risiko, von einer Lawine verschüttet zu werden, abzuschätzen. 

- Aktueller Lawinenlagebericht für Deutschland, Österreich, Schweiz und Italien
- Neigungsmesser
- Höhenmesser
- Kompass
- Risikocheck
- Notruf

Neigungsmesser, schätze die Hangneigung nicht, sondern peile direkt von der Bergkante den Hang an um die Neigung festzustellen.

Risikocheck , schätze dein Risiko mit Hilfe des Warnberichts, der Neigung und der Exposition ab.

Die Lawinenlageberichte werden offline gespeichert. Dadurch kann dieser direkt am Berg nochmal nachgelesen werden, auch wenn kein Handynetz zur Verfügung steht.
Dadurch können auch, wenn Roaming deaktiviert ist, teure Roaminggebühren gespart werden.

Höhenmesser: Überprüfe am Hang deine Höhe.
Kompass: Entscheide über die Exposition mit dem integierten Kompass.

Notruf, Was ist zu tun im Ernstfall, hier nochmal zum Nachschlagen.
